reviews.review_text:
Terrific sounding Aud Very strong representation of the concert experience.  Clear, crisp, and even full bass.  I prefer auds like this over SBDs any day of the week.

Click the Taper's name at the top and see a few other recordings these guys put together, too.
Ditto Crisp and clear may be understating the matter. Extraordinary recording. Thank you!!
A+ Good sounding show.1ST peggy-o after phil married jill, wich was the day before.I love the setlist!might as well DL.

Two nights of spacey Bliss This night and the next are really sweet.  Crappy weather always made for some great indoor shows.   There are flaws, but the boys really deliver with some x-factor jamming.  I prefer the next night over this one, but it is really a package deal with the Playin' thread.

I think this is the better source over the Oade.  Fuller and brighter.  It comes down to those two sources.  Wonder where the boards are?  Probably better off being in the crowd for these two intense shows.

Take a vacation and do this whole tour East to West.  Like to take that ride again.
Best sounding source This is the best sounding source for this show. Very intense version of Playin.

Wow ! Used to love this show on tape but haven't listened in a long time.   This copy has a fantastic AUD sound.  Only listened to the first set so far.   That might as well gave me my first genuine happy moment in quite a while.   Thanks Jerry.    And thanks to the tapers for putting in the hard work.
